properties.Name: EEZ
properties.Description:
The extent of Japan’s EEZ claim has been publicized by the government in maps; for example, this coast guard map shows the full area. We created the EEZ polygon by drawing 200 nm arcs and editing the resulting shape to match the coast guard map. Along its maritime boundary in the East China Sea, Japan has stated its preference to use an equidistant line to delineate the limits of its zone. It also claims an EEZ from the Diaoyu/Senkaku Islands.

Japan’s territorial sea is unusual in being unilaterally reduced to 3 nm in five straits. These straits have been declared in domestic regulations and deposited with the United Nations. We recognize these adjustments but have not included them on the map as they are irrelevant to Japan’s strategic concerns.
